declarations.comments:
Creates a new websocket, where the send and receive types are encoded and decoded as JSON strings
internally.
declarations.title: newWebSocket

declarations.comments: Creates a new websocket, where the send and receive types are monomorphically typed as a String.
declarations.title: newWebSocketString

declarations.comments:
Creates a new websocket, where the send and receive types are expected to be binary-compatible over
the websocket (a `Blob` or `ArrayBuffer`).
declarations.title: newWebSocketBinary

declarations.comments:
Creates a new websocket, where binary data is handled by the binary app when available, otherwise
handled by the string app by default.
declarations.title: newWebSocketBoth

modules.name: WebSocket.Text
modules.comments:
This module relies on `purescript-text-encoding` and the `text-encoding` NPM module
for turning a String into an ArrayBuffer and vise-versa.
